=== Koka City designated tangible cultural property ===
* Stone lantern - There is an inscription of the first year of {{ill|lt=Yasunaga|Q980266|qid=Q980266|1=Kōei}} ({{ill|lt=1342|Q6069|qid=Q6069|1=1342}}) of the {{ill|lt=Nanbokucho period (Japan)|Q264012|qid=Q264012|lt=Nanbokucho period|1=Nanboku-chō period}}, which reveals the year of manufacture.

=== Others ===
* A medicine called "Mizuguchi medicine" was once passed down as a family tradition in the Sekio family of the shrine family, and in {{ill|lt=1882|Q7812|qid=Q7812|1=1882}} (Meiji 15), it was given the name "Antaisan" by the Ministry of Home Affairs. (Japan)|Q1142265|Ministry of Home Affairs}} Approved, "{{ill|lt=Great Japan Place Name Dictionary|Q17213149|qid=Q17213149|1=Dai Nippon Chimei Jisho}}" also includes "{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Daidoruijuhou|1=UNKNOWN}}, and wrote, ``Mizuguchi medicine, Ōmi Province Mizuguchi Shrine celebration Tono no Kaden, originator Omi Takajin Rikiya, heat and cold, daily and occasional thirst, and intestinal motility effect, etc.'', but it has not been passed down at present.
* In the diary of the Shake Sekio family, we can see that in September {{ill|lt=1868|Q7717|qid=Q7717|1=1868}} (first year of the Meiji era), on the occasion of the Emperor Toyuki, {{ill|lt=Imperial envoy|Q11399920|qid=Q11399920|1=Chokushi}} sent {{ill|lt=Masayoshi Uematsu|Q22128646|qid=Q22128646|1=Masayoshi Uematsu}} to this shrine.

